9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1164, L.D. 1746, “An Act to Reduce
10 Dental Disease and Ensure Access to Essential Preventive Dental Care Among Maine
11 Children”
12 Amend the bill in section 2 in the 5th line (page 1, line 14 in L.D.) by inserting after
13 the following: "Project." the following: 'For the purposes of this section, "mobile dental
14 services" means dental services provided at a setting other than a permanent dental clinic.'
15 Amend the bill in section 3 in the 4th line (page 1, line 23 in L.D.) by inserting after
16 the following: "children." the following: 'The department shall ensure that all training and
17 education is provided by licensed dental health professionals.'
18 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 4 and inserting the following:
19 'Sec. 4. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
20 allocations are made.
21 HEALTH AND HUMAN SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
22 Maine Center for Disease Control and Prevention 0143
23 Initiative: Provides funding to provide for, at least every school year in a different public
24 health district, at least one mobile dental services provider until each district has at least
25 one mobile dental services provider.
